{
  "stem": "19210.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, basically, once, once we got them out of the, the water, out of the ship, the main idea was to move them quickly and, and disperse them, so to speak, to a variety of areas.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because most likely than not, the British would always find out when ships come in where they come in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and they would find out where.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they certainly would send someone from the area.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If it was-- in most cases, it was a British military-- civilian police.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, and we tried our best to, to the Haganah commanders to have whatever vehicles were available to us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Again, in such a community as Nahariya where there was about 1,200 people, there was not that many cars, private cars, or-- there was buses, there was trucks, there was some motorcycles, et cetera, et cetera, and, and several of the homes of the natives of Nahariya.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we would bring people into different homes to hide them overnight.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then at the following morning, we would bring them to the station, to the bus station-- again, to trucks, and go to a variety of areas, if it was to a kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In most cases, many kibbutzim were used, because you wouldn't see the police going to a kibbutz-- very, very rare.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The British police would not do that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we did it very quickly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In fact, we had in our-- when we unloaded the Aliyah, there was a refugee that we brought to our home.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "At the time, my wife was-- Miriam was pregnant.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was in the ninth month, I believe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we brought a refugee.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One was upstairs with our neighbor, Mr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Cohn-- C-O-H-N.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And one was in my, in my apartment.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
